Kerry further added that the US would explore ways to increase the limit beyond 100,000 in future years while carrying out background checks to ensure that the refugees have not been infiltrated by terrorists.Ironically, just as Europe is shutting its doors to Syrian refugees, the US is opening its own.Significantly, the countries that have generated most of the refugees are all places where the United States has invaded, overthrown governments, supported insurgencies, or intervened in a civil war. The cap would then rise to 100,000 the following year.Mr. Kerry said that the United States would explore ways to increase the limit beyond 100,000 in future years while carrying out background checks to ensure that the refugees have not been infiltrated by terrorists.‚ÄúThis step is in keeping with America‚Äôs best tradition as a land of second chances and a beacon of hope,‚Äù Mr. Kerry said in his prepared remarks. ‚ÄúAnd it will be accompanied by continued financial contributions to the humanitarian effort ‚Äî not only from the U.S. government, but from the American people. Public school lunches and breakfasts are served through the Federal School Lunch Program. Parents can fill out forms at the beginning of the school year and based on their income, they can qualify for FREE or REDUCED prices for their children. Even if they don't qualify for free or reduced lunch and they eat at the school, a portion of every child's meal is paid for by the federal government. If students have overdue lunch bills, it is because their parents did not pay the remaining amount that was charged after the federal government paid its part.

It broke her heart and frustrated her that those kids who had past due accounts or no money at all got a sandwich consisting of 2 pieces of bread and a slice of cheese, yet school employees got to eat free.  She would stand by and watch her supervisor and fellow cafeteria workers take home the leftovers and toss out what they didn't want.  I remember she confronted the supervisor and was told that it was school policy and that was that.  She retired shortly after.  For the record, she NEVER brought food home nor did she take her lunches at the school.  My grandfather always cooked her breakfast before she left and she always took her own lunch in.
